Preheat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @poblano pepper{1} lengthwise; remove stem and seeds. Trim, then halve @scallions{2} crosswise, separating whites from greens. Thinly slice greens, leaving whites whole. Drain half the @corn{13.4%ounce} and pat dry with #paper towels{} (save the rest for another use).

Toss corn with a drizzle of oil, half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Place poblano halves on other side of baking sheet. Drizzle with oil, then season with remaining Southwest spice and a pinch of salt and pepper. Broil, turning halfway through, until lightly charred, about ~{7%minutes}. Add scallion whites to baking sheet. Continue to broil until charred, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While veggies char, zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{1}, then halve and squeeze 2 TBSP juice into a #medium bowl{}. Dice @roma tomato{1}. Mince @chili pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Stir tomato, a large drizzle of olive oil, and as much chili as you like into bowl with lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and enough water to create a drizzling consistency. Season with salt. Once they are cool enough to handle, roughly chop poblano and scallion whites. In a #large bowl{}, combine poblano, scallion whites, corn, lime zest, half the @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}, and a sprinkle of salt and pepper.

Rub @flour tortilla{2} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} each. Place oiled sides down on a separate baking sheet. Divide filling between one half of each tortilla; fold tortillas in half over filling. Broil until tortillas are lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Flip quesadillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Return to broiler until cheese bubbles, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Cut quesadillas into thirds; divide between plates. Top with crema and salsa. Sprinkle with scallion greens.